\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

-tuple remain in 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof

\series bold
step 3.

\series default
 Define the relation 
\begin_inset Formula $\sim$
\end_inset

 on 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 by setting 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha\sim\beta$
\end_inset

 if 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

 is a cyclic permutation of 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\sim$
\end_inset

