\begin_layout Theorem
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subgroupsofcyclicgroups"

\end_inset

Any subgroup of a cyclic group is cyclic.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 be a cyclic group generated by 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 and let 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

 be a subgroup of 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $H=\left\{ e\right\} $
\end_inset

 then 
\begin_inset Formula $H=\left\langle e\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 is cyclic.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
If 
\begin_inset Formula $H\neq\left\{ e\right\} $
\end_inset

 then 
\begin_inset Formula $a^{n}\in H$
\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $n\in\mathbf{Z}\setminus\left\{ 0\right\} $
\end_inset

.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

 is a subgroup 
\begin_inset Formula $a^{-n}\in H$
\end_inset

 also so we may assume 
\begin_inset Formula $n\in\mathbf{Z}^{+}$
\end_inset

.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 be the least positive integer such that 
\begin_inset Formula $a^{m}\in H$
\end_inset

 .
 We will prove that 
\begin_inset Formula $H=\left\langle a^{m}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

.
 The inclusion 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\langle a^{m}\right\rangle \subseteq H$
\end_inset

 is clear because 
\begin_inset Formula $H\leq G$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $b\in H$
\end_inset

 and write 
\begin_inset Formula $b=a^{n}$
\end_inset

.
 By the division algorithm
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
n=mq+r,\ 0\leq r<m.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
So 
\begin_inset Formula $a^{n}=\left(a^{m}\right)^{q}a^{r}$
\end_inset

 and it follows that 
\begin_inset Formula $a^{r}=\left(a^{m}\right)^{-q}b\in H$
\end_inset

.
 Thus 
\begin_inset Formula $r=0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $b=\left(a^{m}\right)^{q}$
\end_inset

.
 This shows that 
\begin_inset Formula $H\subseteq\left\langle a^{m}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 and we conclude that 
\begin_inset Formula $H=\left\langle a^{m}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

