\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\left(n\right)$
\end_inset

 generators of 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
There is a unique subgroup 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

 of order 
\begin_inset Formula $d$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 and this subgroup has 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\left(d\right)$
\end_inset

 elements of order 
\begin_inset Formula $d$
\end_inset

 by Corollary 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eulertotfun"

\end_inset

.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $g\in G$
\end_inset

 has order 
\begin_inset Formula $d$
\end_inset

 then, by uniqueness, 
\begin_inset Formula $H=\left\langle g\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 so 
\begin_inset Formula $g\in H$
\end_inset

.
 Thus 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

