\begin_layout Section
Order of an element in 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{n}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is easy to compute the order of a permutation, given its cycle type.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Lemma
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "orderofapermutation"

\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma\in S_{n}$
\end_inset

 be a permutation with cycle type 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(n_{1},n_{2},\ldots,n_{r}\right)$
\end_inset

.
 The order of 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

 is the least common multiple of 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{1},n_{2},\ldots,n_{r}$
\end_inset

.
 In particular 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{i}\mid o\left(\left\langle \sigma\right\rangle \right)$
\end_inset

 for each 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 be the order of 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

 and let 
\begin_inset Formula $L=\mathrm{lcm}\left(n_{1},n_{2},\ldots,n_{r}\right)$
\end_inset


\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\strikeout off
\uuline off
\uwave off
\noun off
\color none
.
 Let
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sigma=\rho_{1}\rho_{2}\ldots\rho_{r}
\]

\end_inset

be the decomposition of 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

 into disjoint cycles of lengths 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{1},n_{2},\ldots,n_{r}$
\end_inset

.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho$
\end_inset

's commute by Lemma 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "disjointcyclescommute"

\end_inset

 hence 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sigma^{m}=e=\rho_{1}^{m}\rho_{2}^{m}\ldots\rho_{r}^{m}.
\]

\end_inset

It follows that for each 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\rho_{i}^{m}=e.
\]

\end_inset

By Lemma 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "orderofcycle"

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{i}$
\end_inset

 has order 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{i}$
\end_inset

 hence 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{i}\mid m$
\end_inset

.
 Thus 
\begin_inset Formula $L\mid m$
\end_inset

.
 But
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sigma^{L}=\rho_{1}^{L}\rho_{2}^{L}\ldots\rho_{r}^{L}=e
\]

\end_inset

so 
\begin_inset Formula $m\mid L$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $m=L$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Remark.

\series default
 It follows that if 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 is prime then a permutation of order 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 can only have cycle lengths 1 or 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

