\series bold
First Proof.

\series default
 Consider the map 
\begin_inset Formula $f\,\colon\, H\times K\longrightarrow HK$
\end_inset

 defined by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f\left(\left(h,k\right)\right)=hk.
\]

\end_inset

We note that 
\begin_inset Formula $h_{1}k_{1}=h_{2}k_{2}$
\end_inset

 iff 
\begin_inset Formula $h_{1}^{-1}h_{2}=t=k_{1}k_{2}^{-1}$
\end_inset

 so that 
\begin_inset Formula $t\in H\cap K$
\end_inset

.
