\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Given an aribtrary group 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

, it can be quite hard to determine the conjugacy classes of 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

.
 Here is the most that can be said in general.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Lemma
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "conjugacyabelian"

\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 be a group.
 Then the conjugacy classes all have exactly one element iff 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 is abelian.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
\begin_inset Formula $C_{x}=\left\{ x\right\} $
\end_inset

for all 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in G$
\end_inset

 iff 
\begin_inset Formula $\forall x,\, gxg^{-1}=x\forall\, g\in G$
\end_inset

.
