\begin_layout Theorem
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "ThirdIsoThm"

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 be a normal subgroup of a group 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

 be a subgroup of 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 that contains 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

 is normal then
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
G/H\simeq\frac{G/N}{H/N}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Suppose that 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

 is normal in 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

.
 Define the function 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi\colon G/N\to G/H$
\end_inset

 by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\phi\left(gN\right)=gH.
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 is well defined because 
\begin_inset Formula $g_{1}N=g_{2}N$
\end_inset

 implies 
\begin_inset Formula $g_{1}^{-1}g_{2}\in N$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\subset H$
\end_inset

.
 Hence 
\begin_inset Formula $g_{1}H=g_{2}H$
\end_inset

 .
 Clearly 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 is a homomorphism onto 
\begin_inset Formula $G/H$
\end_inset

 with kernel 
\begin_inset Formula $H/N$
\end_inset

 .
 Hence 
\begin_inset Formula $H/N$
\end_inset

 is normal and by the first isomorphism theorem
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\phi\left(G/N\right)=G/H\simeq\frac{G/N}{H/N}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

